<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-394-920  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 394 920.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  April 26 1990 n1413* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mercury, ATandamp;T team on pan-European satellite data trial. (Cable andamp;Wireless PLC's Mercury Communications Ltd.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tridom Corp. (joint ventures)Mercury Communications PLC (joint ventures).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Joint VentureTelephone CompaniesTelecommunicationsSatellite CommunicationsVery Small Aperture TerminalsNetworksEurope.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MERCURY, ATandamp;T TEAM ON PAN-EUROPEAN SATELLITE DATA TRIALandM;Cable andamp; Wireless Plc's Mercury Communications Ltd has joined forces with ATandamp;TCo's ATandamp;T Tridom in Marietta, Georgia to build a trial satellite network fordata transmission in Europe.andP;  The trial, scheduled to begin this quarter isto help determine the operational and economic feasibility of interactivevery small aperture terminal network services in Europe.andP;  Like two-waysatellite television dishes, very small aperture terminals are earthstationsat customer sites capable of sending as well as receiving data communicationsvia satellite.andP;  Terminals will be installed under the agreement inco-operation with the appropriate PTTs so that if one of the more ludditecontinental PTTs says &quot;no dice&quot;, that country will have to be eliminated fromthe experiment.andP;  Mercury will provide satellite access for the trial and beresponsible for the administration of the transmission service, arranging forcapacity on a Eutelsat satellite, and will manage ground station facilitiesat its hub earth station in London.andP;  ATandamp;T Tridom will run the network andwill provide the remote earthstations with joint responsibility forinstallation and maintenance with Mercury.andO;</TEXT></DOC>